<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
    <head>
        <meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8" />
        <meta name="mobile-web-app-capable" content="yes" />
        <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, user-scalable=no, initial-scale=1.0, minimum-scale=1.0, maximum-scale=1.0" />
        <meta name="description" content="" />
        <meta name="author" content="" />
        <title>Account</title>
        <link rel="stylesheet" href="/static/css/custom.css" />
        <script src="/static/js/bg.js"></script>
    </head>
    <body>
        <div id="window">
            <div id="blur"></div>
            <div class="content center">
                <h2><span class="thinblock">Welcome </span><strong><%= user.getName() %></strong></h2>
                <input type="text" disabled value="<%= token %>"/>
                <h4>Token expires in <span id="expiry">60 minutes</span>.</h4>
                <h2>Option 1 - EVE Mail</h2>
                <p class="desc">Send an EVE Mail to <a href="https://gate.eveonline.com/Mail/Compose/Vincent Eneticum">Vincent Eneticum</a> and use the token provided above for the subject. The character used to send the mail will then be added to your account. This can take up to 15 minutes.</p>
                <h2>Option 2 - 0-access API Key</h2>
                <p class="desc">Go to the <a href="https://community.eveonline.com/support/api-key/CreatePredefined?accessMask=0">API Key Management</a> and set the vCode value to the token (check "No Expiry") and paste the resulting Key ID in the form below</p>
                <form action="/account/add/api" method="post" class="content">
                    <input type="text" name="keyID">
                    <input type="text" name="vCode" value="<%= token %>" disabled="">
                    <input type="submit" value="Submit">
                </form>
                <form action="/account"><button type="submit" >BACK</button></form>
            </div>
        </div>
        <script>
            window.addEventListener("load", function () {
                var minutes = 60;
                var interval = setInterval(function () {
                    document.getElementById("expiry").innerHTML = (--minutes) + " minutes";
                    if(minutes == 0)
                        clearInterval(interval);
                }, 1000 * 60);
            });
        </script>
    </body>
</html>